System Design - Messaging Queue | Message Queue | Kafka

Queue:
 - Generally you send one request & you get response, but when you send so many requests in big servers, it's very important to have processing queue,
  where you send request & 
 they all go in processing queue & it solve one by one.
  - Queue are based on asynchronous communication protocol
  - Queues are also used as fault tolerance; In case of any sevice outage, they can retry the requests.
  - Examples: RabbitMQ, ZeroMQ, ActiveMQ, 	 BeanstalkD